00:57:18.372 --> 00:57:19.560
Shit!

1019
00:57:19.615 --> 00:57:20.747
It's a boy!

1020
00:57:20.802 --> 00:57:22.748
Ya-hoo!

1021
00:57:22.773 --> 00:57:23.966
Whoa, whoa!

1022
00:57:24.018 --> 00:57:27.700
I think a little prayer of thanksgiving
would be in order.

1023
00:57:27.739 --> 00:57:30.653
God damn it to hell,
son of a bitch, she did it!

1024
00:57:30.700 --> 00:57:31.754
Here's to Ruth.

1025
00:57:31.785 --> 00:57:36.451
<i>Idgie always did have a way with words
around the Reverend Scroggins.</i>

1026
00:57:36.842 --> 00:57:37.864
<i>Well...</i>

1027
00:57:37.904 --> 00:57:39.607
<i>Ruth had a baby.</i>

1028
00:57:39.685 --> 00:57:41.764
<i>- She named him Buddy.</i>
- Be careful.

1029
00:57:41.818 --> 00:57:43.389
<i>Buddy Junior.</i>

1030
00:57:43.537 --> 00:57:48.209
<i>And Papa went and borrowed money,
so Ruth and Idgie Could start a Café.</i>

1031
00:57:48.334 --> 00:57:50.975
<i>The Whistle Stop Café.</i>

1032
00:57:55.258 --> 00:57:58.141
♪ <i>When you come by my house</i> ♪

1033
00:57:58.180 --> 00:58:00.492
♪ <i>Come down behind the jail</i> ♪

1034
00:58:00.558 --> 00:58:02.978
♪ <i>I've got a sign on my door</i> ♪

1035
00:58:03.024 --> 00:58:05.440
♪ <i>"Barbecue for sale"</i> ♪

1036
00:58:05.478 --> 00:58:08.151
♪ <i>I'm talking about barbecue</i> ♪

1037
00:58:08.456 --> 00:58:12.096
♪ <i>Only thing I crave</i> ♪

1038
00:58:13.612 --> 00:58:16.877
♪ <i>- And that good-doing' meat</i> ♪
- Here, a room to stay.

1039
00:58:16.932 --> 00:58:20.955
♪ <i>Will carry me to my grave</i> ♪

1040
00:58:21.955 --> 00:58:24.752
♪ <i>I'm selling' it for cheap</i> ♪

1041
00:58:26.612 --> 00:58:29.260
- Miss Idgie, get the door for Papa.
♪ <i>- And if you try one time</i> ♪

1042
00:58:29.291 --> 00:58:31.682
♪ <i>- Boy, you can't get enough</i> ♪
- Papa.

1043
00:58:31.761 --> 00:58:33.020
Big George.

1044
00:58:33.067 --> 00:58:35.832
<i>Miss Ruth, me and the missus
sure do want to thank you for</i>

1045
00:58:35.869 --> 00:58:38.449
- sending that soup over for us last night.
- Mmm-hmm.

1046
00:58:38.474 --> 00:58:40.364
I'll, I'll pay you when I get ahead.

1047
00:58:40.403 --> 00:58:42.794
Oh, you don't owe me a thing, Ocie.

1048
00:58:42.843 --> 00:58:45.269
- Thank you, ma'am.
- I'm just glad they're better.

1049
00:58:45.499 --> 00:58:46.868
How is this, by the way?

1050
00:58:46.893 --> 00:58:48.751
- Oh, it's good.
- It's good. Very good, ma'am.

1051
00:58:48.782 --> 00:58:50.813
I'm not happy till
I see clean plates.

1052
00:58:56.191 --> 00:58:57.800
It can't go on, Idgie.

1053
00:58:57.894 --> 00:59:00.246
I'm talking to you
as a friend now, Idgie.

1054
00:59:00.292 --> 00:59:02.269
There are some people in this town,

1055
00:59:02.301 --> 00:59:03.808
they is paying customers too,

1056
00:59:03.840 --> 00:59:05.949
- but I won't say who.
- Here you go, honey.

1057
00:59:06.107 --> 00:59:10.441
But, there are some people
don't like you selling to coloureds.

1058
00:59:10.777 --> 00:59:12.246
Here you go.

1059
00:59:12.326 --> 00:59:14.334
Well, listen, Grady.
I'll tell you what.

1060
00:59:14.381 --> 00:59:16.867
The next time those
"some people" come in here,

1061
00:59:16.906 --> 00:59:17.961
I'm gonna ask them

1062
00:59:17.986 --> 00:59:21.272
if they don't want anybody to know
who they are under those sheets they wear

1063
00:59:21.297 --> 00:59:25.687
when they go marching around in one
of those stupid parades you boys have.

1064
00:59:25.758 --> 00:59:28.711
How come they don't have enough
sense to change their shoes?

1065
00:59:28.741 --> 00:59:30.383
Now, you just hold on there, Idgie.

1066
00:59:30.422 --> 00:59:32.195
No, y'all ain't fooling anybody, Grady.

1067
00:59:32.227 --> 00:59:36.164
Why, I'd recognise those size 14
clodhoppers you got anywhere.

1068
00:59:36.289 --> 00:59:37.836
Just a minute, now, Idgie.

1069
00:59:37.875 --> 00:59:39.820
Would you like
some more pie, Grady?

1070
00:59:39.866 --> 00:59:41.672
No, thank you, Ruth.

1071
00:59:41.742 --> 00:59:43.390
Psst. Idgie.

1072
00:59:43.461 --> 00:59:45.422
I'll talk to the boys.

1073
00:59:45.547 --> 00:59:48.781
But, you just keep them
on out back there, you hear?

1074
00:59:48.969 --> 00:59:50.344
<i>Bye, Ruth.</i>

1075
00:59:50.417 --> 00:59:51.914
Bye, Grady.

1076
00:59:52.307 --> 00:59:54.930
Why, you're gonna get yourself
in a whole heap of trouble.

1077
00:59:54.955 --> 00:59:55.993
What?

1078
00:59:56.024 --> 00:59:58.140
Grady?
He's harmless.

1079
00:59:58.969 --> 01:00:02.875
Oh, you should have seen
that big ox down by the river.

1080
01:00:03.094 --> 01:00:05.573
Three solid days,
drunk as a dog,

1081
01:00:05.612 --> 01:00:07.184
crying like a baby.

1082
01:00:07.254 --> 01:00:09.926
Cos Joe, that old coloured man
that raised him, had died.

1083
01:00:09.965 --> 01:00:11.863
- Remember that, Sipsey?
- Yes'm.

1084
01:00:11.888 --> 01:00:14.045
But, he sure ain't joking now, is he, son?

1085
01:00:14.076 --> 01:00:14.756
No, ma'am.

1086
01:00:14.787 --> 01:00:17.084
He won't even sit in the same room
and have a meal today.

1087
01:00:17.137 --> 01:00:19.272
Oh, it don't make no kind of sense.

1088
01:00:19.319 --> 01:00:22.413
A big old ox like Grady won't
sit next to a coloured child,

1089
01:00:22.467 --> 01:00:23.779
but he eats eggs...

1090
01:00:23.811 --> 01:00:26.436
shoot right out of a chicken's ass.

1091
01:00:34.940 --> 01:00:37.364
♪ <i>Now, some like it hot</i> ♪

1092
01:00:37.450 --> 01:00:39.934
♪ <i>And some like it cold</i> ♪

1093
01:00:40.036 --> 01:00:44.231
♪ <i>Some take it any way, ♪
♪ any way it's sold</i> ♪

1094
01:00:44.292 --> 01:00:47.075
♪ <i>I'm talking' 'bout barbecue</i> ♪

1095
01:00:47.238 --> 01:00:50.529
♪ <i>Only thing I crave</i> ♪

1096
01:00:50.599 --> 01:00:52.825
Come on, Smokey.
Let's go for a walk.

1097
01:00:52.871 --> 01:00:55.709
♪ <i>And that good-doing' meat</i> ♪

1098
01:00:55.770 --> 01:00:59.600
♪ <i>Going' to take me to my grave</i> ♪

1099
01:01:02.140 --> 01:01:04.921
I'm sorry about spilling
my food in there, ma'am.

1100
01:01:04.978 --> 01:01:06.016
Um...

1101
01:01:06.055 --> 01:01:07.977
I'll just head on.

1102
01:01:17.357 --> 01:01:20.108
Do you see that piece of land over there?

1103
01:01:20.780 --> 01:01:21.796
That...

1104
01:01:21.835 --> 01:01:23.170
That used to be a lake.

1105
01:01:23.219 --> 01:01:24.889
- No.
- Yeah.

1106
01:01:25.389 --> 01:01:27.585
And then this one November,...

1107
01:01:27.740 --> 01:01:29.822
all these ducks come by...

1108
01:01:29.874 --> 01:01:31.986
and they landed on that lake.

1109
01:01:32.146 --> 01:01:36.634
Then the temperature dropped so fast,
the whole lake just froze.

1110
01:01:36.940 --> 01:01:39.662
Then the ducks took off
and took the lake with them.

1111
01:01:40.059 --> 01:01:42.420
Now that lake's somewhere over in Georgia.

1112
01:01:42.517 --> 01:01:44.943
<i>- That's the way I heard it.
- Go on, now.</i>

1113
01:01:59.937 --> 01:02:01.915
God bless you, ma'am.

1114
01:02:12.229 --> 01:02:14.987
♪ <i>Cool down by</i> ♪

1115
01:02:15.042 --> 01:02:16.729
♪ <i>the river banks</i> ♪

1116
01:02:16.792 --> 01:02:19.573
♪ <i>Banks of Jordan</i> ♪

1117
01:02:19.768 --> 01:02:23.120
♪ <i>Cool down by</i> ♪

1118
01:02:23.159 --> 01:02:26.942
♪ <i>The banks of Jordan</i> ♪

1119
01:02:27.261 --> 01:02:30.721
♪ <i>Cool down by the river banks</i> ♪

1120
01:02:30.774 --> 01:02:34.245
- Here, try this.
♪ <i>- The banks of Jordan</i> ♪

1121
01:02:36.893 --> 01:02:38.579
So what do you think?

1122
01:02:38.662 --> 01:02:40.401
They're OK.

1123
01:02:40.911 --> 01:02:42.294
The truth.

1124
01:02:42.368 --> 01:02:43.995
They're um...

1125
01:02:44.582 --> 01:02:46.027
They're...

1126
01:02:47.200 --> 01:02:49.146
They're terrible!

1127
01:02:50.070 --> 01:02:51.834
Oh, well.

1128
01:02:52.725 --> 01:02:55.169
Don't be shy.
Tell me how you feel.

1129
01:02:55.206 --> 01:02:56.849
I will.

1130
01:03:11.249 --> 01:03:13.267
What did you go and do that for?

1131
01:03:15.289 --> 01:03:18.421
I just thought you needed
a little cooling off.

1132
01:03:18.730 --> 01:03:20.360
You're right.

1133
01:03:36.008 --> 01:03:37.914
Try these.

1134
01:03:43.299 --> 01:03:45.573
I think we need to make a little paste.

1135
01:04:05.023 --> 01:04:07.664
What in the name of Christmas
are you two doing?

1136
01:04:07.704 --> 01:04:09.765
She's trying to teach me how to cook!

1137
01:04:09.802 --> 01:04:12.820
Look at those fried green tomatoes.

1138
01:04:17.519 --> 01:04:18.628
You'd better stop this,

1139
01:04:18.660 --> 01:04:20.988
or I'm gonna have to arrest you
for disorderly conduct.

1140
01:04:21.042 --> 01:04:22.878
Oh, arrest us, then.

1141
01:04:22.925 --> 01:04:24.948
- Let me handle this.
- All right.

1142
01:04:24.982 --> 01:04:26.495
Grady.

1143
01:04:30.329 --> 01:04:31.571
Arrest us.

1144
01:04:31.899 --> 01:04:33.282
Go ahead and arrest us.

1145
01:04:35.164 --> 01:04:37.196
Ruth, I have to say it.

1146
01:04:37.313 --> 01:04:39.563
I believe Idgie's been
a bad influence on you.

1147
01:04:39.599 --> 01:04:41.039
I agree.

1148
01:04:42.721 --> 01:04:46.252
♪ <i> I-I-I</i> ♪

1149
01:04:46.666 --> 01:04:49.262
♪ <i> I-I-I</i> ♪

1150
01:04:49.317 --> 01:04:52.333
♪ <i>Don't wanna hear you weep no more</i> ♪

1151
01:04:52.559 --> 01:04:54.151
♪ <i>When I'm gone</i> ♪

1152
01:04:54.197 --> 01:04:56.371
♪ <i>Don't wanna hear you weep</i> ♪

1153
01:04:56.403 --> 01:04:57.676
♪ <i>When I'm gone</i> ♪

1154
01:04:57.713 --> 01:04:59.197
♪ <i> In my grave, Lord</i> ♪

1155
01:04:59.234 --> 01:05:00.846
♪ <i>In my grave</i> ♪

1156
01:05:21.352 --> 01:05:23.212
I'll be back in a minute.

1157
01:05:24.235 --> 01:05:25.993
Y'all keep the show going till then.

1158
01:05:26.048 --> 01:05:27.798
We ain't going nowhere.

1159
01:05:29.734 --> 01:05:32.149
Down again.
Is she still poorly?

1160
01:05:32.901 --> 01:05:34.634
Where's the baby?

1161
01:05:34.750 --> 01:05:36.446
Who are you?

1162
01:05:38.505 --> 01:05:40.415
What do you want?

1163
01:05:40.782 --> 01:05:42.337
Frank!

1164
01:05:45.563 --> 01:05:47.183
Get out of here.

1165
01:05:48.760 --> 01:05:50.011
Get on out of here!

1166
01:05:50.074 --> 01:05:51.871
Go on, get out of here
and leave us alone.

1167
01:05:51.921 --> 01:05:53.941
Come on, now, Ruth.

1168
01:05:54.143 --> 01:05:57.540
You wouldn't deny a father
the right to see his own son,...

1169
01:05:57.606 --> 01:05:59.896
- would you?
<i>- You git, I say.</i>

1170
01:06:00.349 --> 01:06:01.860
Scat you!

1171
01:06:02.082 --> 01:06:03.098
Damn!

1172
01:06:03.138 --> 01:06:05.132
Gimme that.
Let it go!

1173
01:06:12.379 --> 01:06:13.843
Well.

1174
01:06:14.194 --> 01:06:16.062
That's my boy.

1175
01:06:16.672 --> 01:06:18.241
Isn't it?

1176
01:06:23.179 --> 01:06:25.422
<i>Is everything all right, ma'am?</i>

1177
01:06:28.290 --> 01:06:30.602
Our guest is just leaving.

1178
01:06:30.972 --> 01:06:33.344
<i>Come on, Frank, let's go.</i>

1179
01:06:37.109 --> 01:06:38.782
I'll be back.

1180
01:06:40.130 --> 01:06:43.063
In the end, you and the baby
are gonna be back.

1181
01:06:47.247 --> 01:06:48.882
I ain't scared of you.

1182
01:06:48.922 --> 01:06:50.281
No, sir.

1183
01:06:50.399 --> 01:06:51.993
You should be.

1184
01:07:03.431 --> 01:07:05.611
You mind your manners, boy!

1185
01:07:14.345 --> 01:07:16.094
Grady?

1186
01:07:16.946 --> 01:07:20.337
What does Gladys think
of you staying out late and...

1187
01:07:20.396 --> 01:07:24.048
losing all your money to me
in poker night after night?

1188
01:07:26.612 --> 01:07:28.404
She likes it just fine.

1189
01:07:32.881 --> 01:07:34.474
They've got Big George!

1190
01:07:34.530 --> 01:07:35.560
Idgie!

1191
01:07:35.607 --> 01:07:38.459
- Let go of him!
- Idgie, you let me handle this, now.

1192
01:07:38.498 --> 01:07:41.717
We've seen how you treat your niggers
around here and we don't like it.

1193
01:07:41.774 --> 01:07:43.857
Well, I'm the law in these here parts.

1194
01:07:43.912 --> 01:07:47.045
And I really don't care
what you like or you don't like.

1195
01:07:47.141 --> 01:07:49.060
Now, you turn him loose.

1196
01:07:49.302 --> 01:07:52.201
Now, don't get all riled up,
nigger-lover.

1197
01:07:52.287 --> 01:07:54.209
Are you deaf or something?

1198
01:07:54.504 --> 01:07:56.123
I said let him go...

1199
01:07:56.233 --> 01:07:58.373
before you get yourselves
in a whole lot of trouble!

1200
01:07:58.405 --> 01:07:59.646
Calm, calm down.

1201
01:07:59.685 --> 01:08:01.834
We just wanted to have
a little get-together and

1202
01:08:01.881 --> 01:08:04.865
make sure we see
eye to eye on some things.

1203
01:08:05.095 --> 01:08:07.037
You hear me, now?

1204
01:08:08.703 --> 01:08:10.373
Let's let him go, boys.

1205
01:08:10.428 --> 01:08:12.280
We've had enough fun for one night.

1206
01:08:12.334 --> 01:08:13.888
All right, turn him loose.

1207
01:08:13.935 --> 01:08:15.506
- Come on.
- No, Miss Idgie.

1208
01:08:15.531 --> 01:08:17.381
- You're gonna get in trouble.
- Come on.

1209
01:08:19.006 --> 01:08:21.420
Well, now, that's more like it.

1210
01:08:21.825 --> 01:08:24.631
It seems I don't recognise
any of you boys.

1211
01:08:24.753 --> 01:08:27.678
Y'all ain't from Whistle Stop, are you?

1212
01:08:29.996 --> 01:08:31.785
This ought to do it.

1213
01:08:32.066 --> 01:08:34.660
I wanna to thank you, Miss Idgie.

1214
01:08:35.074 --> 01:08:36.863
Oh, forget it.

1215
01:08:37.043 --> 01:08:38.996
You'd have done the same for me.

1216
01:08:40.730 --> 01:08:42.496
Now, try to get some sleep.

1217
01:08:48.928 --> 01:08:50.998
Who the hell were those assholes?

1218
01:08:52.131 --> 01:08:54.107
They's just some old boys from Georgia

1219
01:08:54.139 --> 01:08:56.936
come over here to put
a little scare in you.

1220
01:08:57.412 --> 01:08:59.185
Well, it worked.

1221
01:08:59.826 --> 01:09:02.576
One of 'em was over here
the other day for something, and...

1222
01:09:02.686 --> 01:09:05.180
seen you selling food to coloreds.

1223
01:09:05.321 --> 01:09:08.485
They decided to come back
to shake you up a little bit.

1224
01:09:09.446 --> 01:09:10.625
I told 'em...

1225
01:09:10.680 --> 01:09:12.117
we don't need anybody from Georgia

1226
01:09:12.157 --> 01:09:14.992
coming over here telling us
what we can or cannot do.

1227
01:09:15.038 --> 01:09:19.226
They won't be back.
I guaran-gol-damn-tee you that.

1228
01:09:20.844 --> 01:09:24.063
One other thing,
little Miss Smarty-pants.

1229
01:09:24.946 --> 01:09:28.476
I do not wear a size 14 shoe.

1230
01:09:29.500 --> 01:09:31.907
And I don't much care for parades,...

1231
01:09:32.024 --> 01:09:34.328
bedsheets or otherwise.

1232
01:09:47.849 --> 01:09:49.319
<i>Hey.</i>

1233
01:09:50.862 --> 01:09:52.342
<i>What's the matter?</i>

1234
01:09:52.514 --> 01:09:53.647
It was Frank.

1235
01:09:53.678 --> 01:09:55.482
He saw the baby.

1236
01:09:55.991 --> 01:09:58.983
<i>- Are you sure it was him?</i>
- Yes, I'm sure.

1237
01:09:59.256 --> 01:10:01.983
So that's why those Kluxers were here.

1238
01:10:02.146 --> 01:10:04.061
Let me take him.

1239
01:10:06.907 --> 01:10:08.487
Don't worry.
I mean...

1240
01:10:08.574 --> 01:10:10.034
if he's dumb enough...

1241
01:10:10.105 --> 01:10:14.050
to come back again, Grady and
the Alabama boys will take care of him.

1242
01:10:14.127 --> 01:10:16.136
And if they don't, I'll...

1243
01:10:16.339 --> 01:10:17.902
think of something.

1244
01:10:18.309 --> 01:10:20.315
Don't take any chances.

1245
01:10:20.589 --> 01:10:23.464
Promise me you won't
do anything crazy.

1246
01:10:23.519 --> 01:10:24.722
No matter what.

1247
01:10:24.764 --> 01:10:26.034
Me?

1248
01:10:26.383 --> 01:10:28.026
Not me.

1249
01:10:30.251 --> 01:10:32.313
I'm gonna put him down.

1250
01:10:33.818 --> 01:10:35.657
<i>Hey, little Buddy.</i>

1251
01:10:35.967 --> 01:10:39.118
<i>That was the last
anyone saw of Frank Bennett...</i>

1252
01:10:39.173 --> 01:10:41.353
<i>until the night of the town follies.</i>

1253
01:10:41.446 --> 01:10:45.930
<i>Ruth was away at one of
the Reverend Scroggins' many revivals.</i>

1254
01:10:45.993 --> 01:10:49.375
One thing a woman expects
when she gets married...

1255
01:10:49.406 --> 01:10:50.719
is sympathy.

1256
01:10:50.774 --> 01:10:53.479
Well, haven't you got that
since you married me?

1257
01:10:53.502 --> 01:10:54.852
I sure have...

1258
01:10:54.931 --> 01:10:56.946
from the whole town.

1259
01:11:28.934 --> 01:11:29.981
Hey there!

1260
01:11:30.027 --> 01:11:32.004
Miss Idgie,
you've got to come quick.

1261
01:11:32.207 --> 01:11:35.239
Well, the show's hardly begun.

1262
01:11:35.549 --> 01:11:37.512
You've got to come quick now.

1263
01:11:37.559 --> 01:11:38.778
You hear me?

1264
01:11:40.824 --> 01:11:42.309
Run now and get help!

1265
01:11:42.341 --> 01:11:43.628
- Where is the baby?
- Go get help, quick!

1266
01:11:43.659 --> 01:11:45.574
- Run!
- Never mind.

1267
01:12:05.641 --> 01:12:07.391
Excuse me, sir.

1268
01:12:07.766 --> 01:12:12.188
I don't believe you should be
going anywhere with Ruth's baby.

1269
01:12:58.389 --> 01:12:59.709
Thank you.

1270
01:12:59.763 --> 01:13:00.850
Hi there.

1271
01:13:00.888 --> 01:13:02.451
What can I do for you boys?

1272
01:13:02.484 --> 01:13:04.248
- Idgie.
- Grady.

1273
01:13:04.304 --> 01:13:06.990
This here is Sheriff Curtis Smoote.

1274
01:13:07.039 --> 01:13:08.974
- Hi there.
- He's over here from Georgia.

1275
01:13:09.005 --> 01:13:11.576
- Oh.
- And he's looking for a fella.

1276
01:13:13.768 --> 01:13:15.268
Do you recognise him?

1277
01:13:15.324 --> 01:13:17.354
- No.
- That's my husband.

1278
01:13:17.379 --> 01:13:19.908
But, I haven't seen him in months.

1279
01:13:20.416 --> 01:13:24.346
Well, I heard he got run over
by a Brinks armoured truck.

1280
01:13:24.440 --> 01:13:26.065
What's he done?

1281
01:13:26.119 --> 01:13:27.596
Nothing that we know of.

1282
01:13:27.643 --> 01:13:30.214
We're trying to find out
what's been did to him.

1283
01:13:30.260 --> 01:13:34.496
He told his hired man he was coming
over here to see his wife and baby, but...

1284
01:13:34.604 --> 01:13:37.299
he ain't never showed up back home.

1285
01:13:37.901 --> 01:13:41.963
Hell, I told him if he showed up
in this town, we'd all have known.

1286
01:13:42.271 --> 01:13:44.815
It looks a little sissified to me.

1287
01:13:45.229 --> 01:13:46.533
From what I hear,

1288
01:13:46.581 --> 01:13:50.611
most of you boys over there in Georgia
are a little light on your feet.

1289
01:13:51.181 --> 01:13:53.127
That's the way I heard it.

1290
01:13:54.107 --> 01:13:56.213
Could I interest you in some pie?

1291
01:13:56.276 --> 01:13:57.440
No, ma'am.

1292
01:13:57.486 --> 01:14:00.111
But, that barbecue sure smells good.

1293
01:14:00.338 --> 01:14:04.026
Best damn barbecue
in the state of Alabama.

1294
01:14:32.894 --> 01:14:34.412
Here you go.

1295
01:14:34.592 --> 01:14:35.834
That's your fourth one today.

1296
01:14:35.874 --> 01:14:38.280
I swear you're about
to eat up all my barbecue.

1297
01:14:38.351 --> 01:14:39.928
Sit down.

1298
01:14:41.833 --> 01:14:43.295
Sit down.

1299
01:14:45.590 --> 01:14:48.145
You ain't fooling me, girly girl.

1300
01:14:48.357 --> 01:14:50.474
I know who you are.

1301
01:14:51.072 --> 01:14:54.903
I heard from Bennett's hired hand that
you threatened to kill Frank Bennett.

1302
01:14:54.997 --> 01:14:57.700
Now, he ain't showed up dead yet.

1303
01:14:57.804 --> 01:15:00.083
But if he does, you're in
a whole mess of trouble.

1304
01:15:00.138 --> 01:15:01.778
You understand?

1305
01:15:02.521 --> 01:15:04.966
What we're talking about
is murder here.

1306
01:15:05.192 --> 01:15:08.544
Running afoul of the law, and
don't nobody get away with that,

1307
01:15:08.591 --> 01:15:11.796
not even a bunch of
Alabama smart alecks.

1308
01:15:12.648 --> 01:15:13.702
Now.

1309
01:15:13.741 --> 01:15:15.624
If I find so much as
a hair of his head,

1310
01:15:15.649 --> 01:15:18.491
I'll arrest you faster than
you can slap a tick.

1311
01:15:18.991 --> 01:15:20.741
<i>Cos I'm the law.</i>

1312
01:15:20.839 --> 01:15:22.999
And you can't beat the law.

1313
01:15:43.988 --> 01:15:45.410
Hey there.

1314
01:15:47.270 --> 01:15:48.972
Tell me what he said.

1315
01:15:49.090 --> 01:15:50.106
Who?

1316
01:15:50.153 --> 01:15:51.574
Smoote's?

1317
01:15:53.551 --> 01:15:55.106
I told you.
He said...

1318
01:15:55.153 --> 01:15:58.199
that was the best damn
barbecue he ever had.

1319
01:15:58.309 --> 01:15:59.863
That's all?

1320
01:16:00.324 --> 01:16:02.519
- No.
- What else?

1321
01:16:03.910 --> 01:16:06.324
He said, pie was pretty good too.

1322
01:16:12.463 --> 01:16:15.002
You sure you ain't never
seen this man before?

1323
01:16:15.072 --> 01:16:16.931
Yes, sir.
I've already told you.

1324
01:16:16.987 --> 01:16:18.541
I ain't never seen him.

1325
01:16:18.783 --> 01:16:22.207
You'd do anything for Miss Idgie now,
wouldn't you, boy?

1326
01:16:24.155 --> 01:16:25.613
Yes, sir.

1327
01:16:28.391 --> 01:16:30.050
Would you kill for her?

1328
01:16:30.882 --> 01:16:32.727
Did you kill for her?

1329
01:16:40.226 --> 01:16:41.445
No, sir.

1330
01:16:42.171 --> 01:16:45.899
Well, now, maybe one of these days
you'll tell the truth.

1331
01:16:48.918 --> 01:16:51.490
Just remember, we hang
lying niggers in Georgia

1332
01:16:51.522 --> 01:16:54.264
just as fast as
they do in Alabama.

1333
01:16:55.227 --> 01:16:56.587
Yes, sir.

1334
01:16:56.692 --> 01:16:58.131
I remember.

1335
01:17:01.100 --> 01:17:06.532
♪ <i>A God</i> ♪

1336
01:17:07.325 --> 01:17:10.133
♪ <i>To</i> ♪

1337
01:17:10.476 --> 01:17:19.602
♪ <i>Glorify</i> ♪

1338
01:17:19.898 --> 01:17:23.149
♪ <i>A never-dying soul to save</i> ♪

1339
01:17:23.585 --> 01:17:28.484
♪ <i>And fit it for the sky</i> ♪

1340
01:17:37.626 --> 01:17:39.079
Sorry.

1341
01:17:40.038 --> 01:17:42.149
What are you doing in here?

1342
01:17:42.345 --> 01:17:44.477
No milk in the house.

1343
01:17:45.297 --> 01:17:46.868
Where were you?

1344
01:17:46.923 --> 01:17:50.227
Taking care of business,
having a good time.

1345
01:17:52.966 --> 01:17:54.821
I've been thinking.

1346
01:17:55.812 --> 01:17:59.508
Maybe, I should move on,
because of Frank and all.

1347
01:18:00.857 --> 01:18:02.446
I just...

1348
01:18:02.844 --> 01:18:04.950
don't want you to feel like...

1349
01:18:05.167 --> 01:18:07.753
you have to look out for us.

1350
01:18:08.907 --> 01:18:10.365
<i>I just...<i>

1351
01:18:10.483 --> 01:18:12.188
don't want to be selfish,
that's all.

1352
01:18:12.219 --> 01:18:15.165
Maybe if I wasn't here,
you'd settle down.

1353
01:18:15.415 --> 01:18:18.352
I'm as settled as I ever hope to be.

1354
01:18:33.840 --> 01:18:35.160
Then...

1355
01:18:35.214 --> 01:18:37.824
why can't you tell me
where you were?

1356
01:18:48.676 --> 01:18:50.504
I had a dream...

1357
01:18:50.793 --> 01:18:52.208
the other night.

1358
01:18:52.268 --> 01:18:53.965
I dreamt that...

1359
01:18:54.129 --> 01:18:56.418
Buddy was gone.

1360
01:18:57.676 --> 01:18:59.160
I ran to his crib...

1361
01:18:59.200 --> 01:19:02.098
and there he was,
sleeping like an angel.

1362
01:19:02.201 --> 01:19:03.645
And you know...

1363
01:19:03.825 --> 01:19:07.583
I thanked God for letting me
still have Buddy.

1364
01:19:07.936 --> 01:19:10.191
And I remembered...

1365
01:19:10.629 --> 01:19:12.762
having the same reaction...

1366
01:19:12.872 --> 01:19:14.560
after Frank would beat me,

1367
01:19:14.582 --> 01:19:18.105
thanking the Lord for giving me
the strength to take it.

1368
01:19:18.162 --> 01:19:19.889
And I remembered...

1369
01:19:20.483 --> 01:19:24.412
thanking the Lord for
each day that my mother lived.

1370
01:19:25.915 --> 01:19:29.211
Even when she was
spitting up blood and...

1371
01:19:29.360 --> 01:19:31.431
praying for me to kill her.

1372
01:19:33.188 --> 01:19:35.251
I looked in my mother's eyes,

1373
01:19:35.304 --> 01:19:37.391
pleading for me to help her.

1374
01:19:37.440 --> 01:19:39.094
And all I could do...

1375
01:19:39.149 --> 01:19:40.891
was pray.

1376
01:19:45.807 --> 01:19:47.276
While...

1377
01:19:47.400 --> 01:19:48.721
While you were gone,

1378
01:19:48.766 --> 01:19:50.541
as I was holding Buddy,
I thought,...

1379
01:19:50.580 --> 01:19:51.799
if that...

1380
01:19:51.846 --> 01:19:53.260
bastard,...

1381
01:19:53.448 --> 01:19:57.494
Frank Bennett, ever tries
to take my child,...

1382
01:19:59.112 --> 01:20:00.963
I won't pray.

1383
01:20:02.528 --> 01:20:04.666
I'll break his neck.

1384
01:20:08.357 --> 01:20:11.610
Ruth, you don't have to worry
about Frank Bennett any more.

1385
01:20:12.613 --> 01:20:14.618
How can you say that?

1386
01:20:14.891 --> 01:20:16.391
It's his child too.

1387
01:20:16.446 --> 01:20:18.704
He won't give up on his blood.

1388
01:20:19.096 --> 01:20:21.938
I'm only gonna tell you this one time.

1389
01:20:24.439 --> 01:20:27.423
Frank Bennett won't be
bothering you no more.

1390
01:20:27.580 --> 01:20:29.469
You understand?

1391
01:20:33.133 --> 01:20:34.911
You killed him...

1392
01:20:36.282 --> 01:20:37.790
didn't you?

1393
01:20:38.054 --> 01:20:39.518
No.

1394
01:20:48.384 --> 01:20:50.180
You don't believe me.

1395
01:20:50.984 --> 01:20:53.656
Right now, I don't know
what to believe.

1396
01:20:56.317 --> 01:20:59.922
Believe me when I tell you
I don't want you to move out.

1397
01:21:11.824 --> 01:21:15.639
♪ <i>If I can help</i> ♪

1398
01:21:17.318 --> 01:21:20.639
♪ <i>Somebody</i> ♪

1399
01:21:22.683 --> 01:21:25.936
♪ <i>As I go</i> ♪

1400
01:21:26.068 --> 01:21:27.482
Finally.

1401
01:21:28.904 --> 01:21:29.904
Thanks.

1402
01:21:29.954 --> 01:21:31.811
I've been out here all day.

1403
01:21:32.424 --> 01:21:35.598
♪ If I can show

1404
01:21:35.993 --> 01:21:41.496
♪ <i>Somebody</i> ♪

1405
01:21:42.254 --> 01:21:45.481
♪ <i>That they're traveling</i> ♪

1406
01:21:45.964 --> 01:21:48.183
♪ <i>Traveling wrong</i> ♪

1407
01:21:49.949 --> 01:21:52.589
♪ <i>Then my living</i> ♪

1408
01:21:53.160 --> 01:21:55.480
♪ <i>Shall not</i> ♪

1409
01:21:55.574 --> 01:21:58.996
♪ <i>No, it shall not be in vain</i> ♪

1410
01:21:59.073 --> 01:22:00.722
Uh, excuse me.

1411
01:22:00.762 --> 01:22:02.537
Uh, I was waiting for that space.

1412
01:22:02.576 --> 01:22:03.998
Yeah? Tough!

1413
01:22:04.043 --> 01:22:06.547
Face it, lady,
we're younger and faster.

1414
01:22:27.460 --> 01:22:29.394
Towanda.

1415
01:22:36.313 --> 01:22:38.508
- Hey!
- Yeah!

1416
01:22:39.196 --> 01:22:42.805
Whoa, whoa!

1417
01:22:46.998 --> 01:22:49.725
Towanda!

1418
01:22:53.886 --> 01:22:55.928
Yes, ma'am!

1419
01:22:56.022 --> 01:22:59.272
Whoa, whoa!

1420
01:23:01.587 --> 01:23:02.860
Help!

1421
01:23:02.970 --> 01:23:04.040
Someone!

1422
01:23:04.078 --> 01:23:06.743
What are you doing?
Are you crazy?

1423
01:23:06.883 --> 01:23:08.110
Face it, girls.

1424
01:23:08.163 --> 01:23:10.805
I'm older and I have more insurance.

1425
01:23:19.885 --> 01:23:22.018
I never get mad,
Mrs. Threadgoode.

1426
01:23:22.042 --> 01:23:23.049
Never.

1427
01:23:23.094 --> 01:23:25.549
The way I was raised,
it was bad manners.

1428
01:23:25.617 --> 01:23:27.042
Well, I got mad.

1429
01:23:27.104 --> 01:23:28.776
And it felt terrific.

1430
01:23:28.815 --> 01:23:32.151
I felt like I could beat the shit
out of all those punks.

1431
01:23:32.197 --> 01:23:33.378
Excuse my language.

1432
01:23:33.403 --> 01:23:35.005
Just beat 'em to a pulp.

1433
01:23:35.057 --> 01:23:37.120
Beat 'em till they begged for mercy.

1434
01:23:37.164 --> 01:23:39.104
Towanda the avenger.

1435
01:23:39.159 --> 01:23:42.558
And after I, after I wipe out
all the punks in this world,

1436
01:23:42.590 --> 01:23:44.989
I'll take on the wife-beaters
like Frank Bennett...

1437
01:23:45.044 --> 01:23:46.786
and machine-gun their genitals.

1438
01:23:48.724 --> 01:23:50.895
Towanda will go on the rampage.

1439
01:23:50.937 --> 01:23:53.749
I'll put tiny little bombs in
Penthouse and Playboy,

1440
01:23:53.788 --> 01:23:55.781
so they'll explode
when you open them.

1441
01:23:55.849 --> 01:23:57.999
And I'll ban all fashion models

1442
01:23:58.062 --> 01:24:01.187
who weigh less than 130 pounds.

1443
01:24:02.124 --> 01:24:05.710
And I'll give half the military budget
to people over 65.

1444
01:24:05.761 --> 01:24:08.522
And declare wrinkles sexually desirable.

1445
01:24:08.593 --> 01:24:09.788
Towanda...

1446
01:24:09.843 --> 01:24:13.163
righter of wrongs,
queen beyond compare.

1447
01:24:13.366 --> 01:24:16.741
How many of them hormones
are you taking, honey?

1448
01:24:24.184 --> 01:24:28.319
♪ <i>Oh, when you give more than you get</i> ♪

1449
01:24:28.374 --> 01:24:30.187
♪ <i>You're in danger</i> ♪

1450
01:24:30.236 --> 01:24:31.840
Well, honey...

1451
01:24:32.185 --> 01:24:34.598
what I can't understand is,

1452
01:24:34.749 --> 01:24:36.590
how in the hell...

1453
01:24:36.794 --> 01:24:38.411
you could hit someone...

1454
01:24:38.473 --> 01:24:40.419
six times by accident?

1455
01:24:40.477 --> 01:24:41.778
Oh, Ed.

1456
01:24:41.856 --> 01:24:44.762
Don't make such a big deal about it.

1457
01:24:51.030 --> 01:24:52.538
What the hell's this?

1458
01:24:52.595 --> 01:24:54.679
That's a low-cholesterol meal.

1459
01:24:54.762 --> 01:24:56.217
Happy Valentine's.

1460
01:24:56.279 --> 01:24:57.904
♪ <i>That's danger</i> ♪

1461
01:24:57.943 --> 01:25:00.182
♪ <i>And heartbreak dead ahead</i> ♪

1462
01:25:00.237 --> 01:25:01.323
God!

1463
01:25:01.354 --> 01:25:03.518
Are you trying to kill me?

1464
01:25:03.583 --> 01:25:06.455
If I was gonna kill you,
I'd use my hands.

1465
01:25:06.850 --> 01:25:10.884
♪ Stop! In the name of love ♪

1466
01:25:10.944 --> 01:25:14.221
♪ Before you break my heart ♪

1467
01:25:14.270 --> 01:25:16.940
♪ Think it over ♪

1468
01:25:18.151 --> 01:25:20.538
♪ Think it over ♪

1469
01:25:23.154 --> 01:25:25.787
I'm worried about
my little friend Evelyn.

1470
01:25:25.880 --> 01:25:30.818
She said her husband, Ed, would just be
sitting around watching his sports on TV,

1471
01:25:30.892 --> 01:25:34.162
and she has an urge to hit him
in the head with a baseball bat.

1472
01:25:34.192 --> 01:25:37.077
Oh hell, that seems normal to me.

1473
01:25:37.592 --> 01:25:39.146
- Hi, Janeen.
- Mmm-hmm.

1474
01:25:39.181 --> 01:25:41.685
Hi, Mrs. Threadgoode.
Would you like some crudités?

1475
01:25:41.710 --> 01:25:43.100
Oh, thank you, Evelyn, but...

1476
01:25:43.171 --> 01:25:45.757
this raw stuff don't
sit good with me.

1477
01:25:46.023 --> 01:25:47.702
Mrs. Threadgoode...

1478
01:25:47.788 --> 01:25:50.100
you have to tell me something.

1479
01:25:50.258 --> 01:25:52.608
Did Idgie murder
Frank Bennett or not?

1480
01:25:52.659 --> 01:25:54.952
Well, hold your horses, honey.

1481
01:25:55.200 --> 01:25:56.889
Where were we?

1482
01:25:58.278 --> 01:26:00.607
You didn't kill Ed,
now, did you?

1483
01:26:01.046 --> 01:26:02.435
Not yet.

1484
01:26:02.533 --> 01:26:04.208
Oh, good.

1485
01:26:04.686 --> 01:26:06.123
Anyway.

1486
01:26:06.201 --> 01:26:09.958
Five years had passed
since Frank Bennett disappeared.

1487
01:26:10.143 --> 01:26:14.279
<i>And Smokey Lonesome had been missing
ever since that same terrible night.</i>

1488
01:26:14.337 --> 01:26:17.115
<i>I remember the day
when he showed up again.</i>

1489
01:26:18.212 --> 01:26:19.990
My God, son.

1490
01:26:20.230 --> 01:26:22.684
You're the spitting image of Ruth.

1491
01:26:22.837 --> 01:26:24.348
Buddy Threadgoode Junior.

1492
01:26:24.388 --> 01:26:25.888
Nice to meet you, sir.

1493
01:26:25.985 --> 01:26:27.880
Well, sir, Smokey Lonesome.

1494
01:26:28.137 --> 01:26:32.100
<i>Curtis Smoote was making
one of his visits to Whistle Stop, Alabama.</i>

1495
01:26:32.135 --> 01:26:35.841
<i>Still hunting and pecking
for any scrap of evidence about</i>

1496
01:26:35.887 --> 01:26:37.942
Frank Bennett's whereabouts.

1497
01:26:37.989 --> 01:26:39.881
- Who wants to begin?
- Oh, I do!

1498
01:26:39.920 --> 01:26:41.434
- Miss Ruth, I do.
- I do, Miss Ruth.

1499
01:26:41.473 --> 01:26:42.911
- I do, Miss Ruth.
- Thank you.

1500
01:26:42.979 --> 01:26:45.528
All right,
we'll begin on page five.

1501
01:26:45.568 --> 01:26:48.848
<i>Life has a funny way
of working things out.</i>

1502
01:26:49.032 --> 01:26:50.747
Well, hey there!

1503
01:26:50.810 --> 01:26:52.523
<i>Smokey!</i>

1504
01:26:53.304 --> 01:26:55.703
- Idgie?
- Smokey Lonesome.

1505
01:26:55.929 --> 01:26:58.195
Well, if it isn't old home week!

1506
01:26:58.229 --> 01:26:59.505
How are you?

1507
01:26:59.560 --> 01:27:01.912
Well, I'm rattling but I'm rolling.

1508
01:27:01.964 --> 01:27:04.146
Well, what brings you to these pans?

1509
01:27:04.237 --> 01:27:05.497
The smell of good cooking.

1510
01:27:05.529 --> 01:27:07.122
Hey, Smokey.

1511
01:27:07.630 --> 01:27:10.247
- Sipsey.
- Well, let me fix you some lunch.

1512
01:27:10.329 --> 01:27:14.636
I think you know just about everybody
except maybe Curtis Smoote.

1513
01:27:14.685 --> 01:27:17.282
He's an officer from over
Valdosta, Georgia.

1514
01:27:17.333 --> 01:27:20.490
He's been looking for the same man
for almost five years.

1515
01:27:20.545 --> 01:27:22.740
Very stubborn fella.

1516
01:27:22.844 --> 01:27:25.109
<i>He loves our barbecue.</i>

1517
01:27:26.276 --> 01:27:27.949
<i>Mommy!</i>

1518
01:27:28.000 --> 01:27:29.773
<i>Mommy, help!</i>

1519
01:27:29.828 --> 01:27:31.305
Buddy!

1520
01:27:36.041 --> 01:27:37.932
Buddy. Buddy!

1521
01:27:37.971 --> 01:27:39.651
- Everybody out of the way.
- Let me in.

1522
01:27:39.683 --> 01:27:41.018
Give him here.
Give him here.

1523
01:27:41.057 --> 01:27:42.761
- Get him to the doctor, now!
- Come on.

1524
01:27:42.799 --> 01:27:44.533
Let him go.
I got him. Let him go.

1525
01:27:44.588 --> 01:27:46.639
- Please, hurry!
- I know. Let me with him.

1526
01:27:46.664 --> 01:27:47.723
You're gonna be all right.

1527
01:27:47.748 --> 01:27:49.319
- Open the door!
- He's gonna be fine.

1528
01:27:49.362 --> 01:27:50.885
All right, calm down.

1529
01:27:51.190 --> 01:27:52.580
Put him, yeah.
Put him in the back.

1530
01:27:52.605 --> 01:27:55.124
Get him in the car.
It's all right, honey.

1531
01:28:16.307 --> 01:28:19.827
I can understand
having a funeral for an arm.

1532
01:28:19.921 --> 01:28:23.934
I just don't know why
she insists on calling him "Stump"?

1533
01:28:24.199 --> 01:28:26.958
Well, she said everybody else
is gonna be calling him that.

1534
01:28:26.989 --> 01:28:29.481
So we might just as well be the first.

1535
01:28:31.667 --> 01:28:34.965
<i>Okay, ice cream and cakes
for everybody in the café.</i>

1536
01:28:35.022 --> 01:28:36.929
Go on.

1537
01:28:37.178 --> 01:28:39.983
- Ice cream and cake.
- All right, I am first.

1538
01:28:41.741 --> 01:28:45.975
My daddy always used to say
there was a separate God for children.

1539
01:28:48.795 --> 01:28:52.334
<i>The good Lord was
watching over Stump that day.</i>

1540
01:28:52.664 --> 01:28:55.615
<i>But then, it started to rain that month.</i>

1541
01:28:55.764 --> 01:29:00.600
<i>And it rained and it rained
and it flooded parts of Whistle Stop.</i>

1542
01:29:00.966 --> 01:29:03.782
<i>And that's why Grady's
deputy stumbled on to</i>

1543
01:29:03.829 --> 01:29:06.056
<i>Frank Bennett's pick-up truck.</i>

1544
01:29:06.247 --> 01:29:10.688
<i>And I just knew Idgie'd
never get out of this mess.</i>

1545
01:29:10.726 --> 01:29:12.446
Now, are you in or out?

1546
01:29:12.540 --> 01:29:14.461
Remember, Ruth,
I didn't take any cards.

1547
01:29:14.501 --> 01:29:16.712
Look at me, Idgie Threadgoode.
Let me see your face.

1548
01:29:16.758 --> 01:29:18.719
- Idgie, I have to talk to you.
- You're bluffing.

1549
01:29:18.829 --> 01:29:21.649
Hi, Grady, why don't you sit in?
I'll deal you a new hand.

1550
01:29:21.674 --> 01:29:22.860
Gladys won't mind.

1551
01:29:22.902 --> 01:29:24.649
In private, Idgie.

1552
01:29:25.068 --> 01:29:26.850
Excuse us, Ruth.

1553
01:29:28.233 --> 01:29:29.553
Well.

1554
01:29:30.022 --> 01:29:32.389
I'm just trying to teach you
not to fall for any tricks.

1555
01:29:32.427 --> 01:29:34.615
You're doing a great job.

1556
01:29:43.808 --> 01:29:45.813
What's your hurry?

1557
01:29:45.974 --> 01:29:48.073
And what is so important?

1558
01:29:51.006 --> 01:29:52.287
What's that?

1559
01:29:52.353 --> 01:29:55.683
Somebody found
Frank Bennett's truck in the river.

1560
01:29:56.730 --> 01:29:58.793
What's that got to do with me?

1561
01:29:58.883 --> 01:30:02.457
Well, officially, you and Big George
are under arrest for murder.

1562
01:30:02.668 --> 01:30:05.250
You're in my custody until tomorrow.

1563
01:30:05.420 --> 01:30:08.968
I'm supposed to take you over to Georgia
first thing in the morning.

1564
01:30:09.996 --> 01:30:12.269
Unless, of course--

1565
01:30:12.822 --> 01:30:15.035
Well, some people have been known

1566
01:30:15.067 --> 01:30:18.051
to pack up and sneak out of town
in the middle of the night.

1567
01:30:22.029 --> 01:30:24.145
What about Big George?

1568
01:30:24.897 --> 01:30:26.794
Well, the way I figure it,...

1569
01:30:26.856 --> 01:30:29.474
they'd be satisfied if they had him.

1570
01:30:30.409 --> 01:30:32.414
Idgie, this is serious.

1571
01:30:32.505 --> 01:30:34.817
We're talking murder of a white man.

1572
01:30:34.930 --> 01:30:36.989
Someone's gonna have to pay.

1573
01:30:37.239 --> 01:30:39.301
Nobody wants to hang a woman.

1574
01:30:41.598 --> 01:30:43.270
No deal.

1575
01:30:43.911 --> 01:30:46.505
Hey, Idgie, I know how
you feel about Big George.

1576
01:30:46.536 --> 01:30:48.249
Hell, we all do.

1577
01:30:48.420 --> 01:30:51.163
But, these are just the facts of life.

1578
01:30:54.617 --> 01:30:56.261
I can't do that.

1579
01:30:56.417 --> 01:30:58.683
Take me to jail if you have to.

1580
01:30:59.280 --> 01:31:01.862
Well, that's what I thought you'd say!

1581
01:31:02.121 --> 01:31:04.665
Cos you are absolutely,
unconditionally,

1582
01:31:04.708 --> 01:31:08.704
positively the most stubborn person
I've ever known in my life!

1583
01:31:10.587 --> 01:31:15.310
<i>So, Idgie and Big George went
to the county jail in Valdosta,...</i>

1584
01:31:15.393 --> 01:31:18.841
<i>to await trial for the murder
of Frank Bennett.</i>

1585
01:31:19.231 --> 01:31:21.401
<i>They didn't have to wait too long.</i>

1586
01:31:21.458 --> 01:31:23.270
Did you know Frank Bennett?

1587
01:31:23.338 --> 01:31:24.661
No, sir.

1588
01:31:25.006 --> 01:31:26.192
You mean to tell me...

1589
01:31:26.232 --> 01:31:28.661
you never met the man
whose wife, Ruth,...

1590
01:31:28.708 --> 01:31:30.388
is your business partner?

1591
01:31:30.461 --> 01:31:31.770
<i>That's right.</i>

1592
01:31:31.838 --> 01:31:34.176
And you never threatened
to kill Frank Bennett,...

1593
01:31:34.255 --> 01:31:38.646
at his home in front of
his hired man, in June of 1932,...

1594
01:31:38.686 --> 01:31:41.170
the same Frank Bennett
you did not know?

1595
01:31:41.240 --> 01:31:43.715
<i>Oh, that was me, all right.</i>

1596
01:31:43.779 --> 01:31:46.185
<i>I thought you wanted to know
if we'd ever met.</i>

1597
01:31:46.232 --> 01:31:48.209
<i>The answer's "no". Um...</i>

1598
01:31:48.422 --> 01:31:50.834
<i>I threatened to kill him, but...</i>

1599
01:31:50.974 --> 01:31:53.733
we were never what you might say,
properly introduced.

1600
01:31:53.763 --> 01:31:56.771
Is it not true that
in September of 1932,

1601
01:31:56.796 --> 01:32:00.193
you came to Valdosta and took
Frank Bennett's wife and child

1602
01:32:00.232 --> 01:32:01.700
back to Alabama with you?

1603
01:32:01.747 --> 01:32:03.177
Mmm, just the wife.

1604
01:32:03.208 --> 01:32:04.372
The child came later.

1605
01:32:04.420 --> 01:32:06.122
How much later?

1606
01:32:06.388 --> 01:32:08.958
The usual.
Nine months.

1607
01:32:09.497 --> 01:32:11.779
Well, I suggest that you bribed...

1608
01:32:11.823 --> 01:32:14.661
this poor weak woman
with promises of...

1609
01:32:14.724 --> 01:32:16.318
liquor and money...

1610
01:32:16.380 --> 01:32:17.538
and she lost...

1611
01:32:17.585 --> 01:32:20.130
control of her senses, momentarily.

1612
01:32:20.175 --> 01:32:23.286
And when her husband came back
to get her and take her home,...

1613
01:32:23.336 --> 01:32:24.927
you and your coloured man...

1614
01:32:24.974 --> 01:32:28.372
murdered him in cold blood.

1615
01:32:29.569 --> 01:32:30.930
No, sir.

1616
01:32:31.235 --> 01:32:32.258
Well...

1617
01:32:32.297 --> 01:32:36.109
Where were you on the night of
September 30th, 1933?

1618
01:32:36.156 --> 01:32:38.484
I was at the town hall,
doing a show.

1619
01:32:38.523 --> 01:32:40.148
And after that?

1620
01:32:40.336 --> 01:32:42.227
I was over at my mother's house.

1621
01:32:42.260 --> 01:32:44.188
Oh, yeah?
Who was with you?

1622
01:32:44.281 --> 01:32:46.408
Just Big George and myself.

1623
01:32:46.435 --> 01:32:48.977
What about your mother?
Can she confirm that?

1624
01:32:49.023 --> 01:32:51.180
No, sir.
She died a year ago.

1625
01:32:51.242 --> 01:32:53.758
Well, I'm sorry to hear that.
But, Miss Threadgoode,

1626
01:32:53.789 --> 01:32:57.305
you expect 12 intelligent men
to believe you,...

1627
01:32:57.385 --> 01:33:00.236
although one witness is dead
and the other is a coloured man

1628
01:33:00.284 --> 01:33:01.510
known to be a...

1629
01:33:01.555 --> 01:33:03.617
worthless, no-good, lying nigger?

1630
01:33:03.642 --> 01:33:06.316
You expect these men
to take your word for it

1631
01:33:06.361 --> 01:33:08.781
<i>just because you say so?</i>

1632
01:33:08.808 --> 01:33:13.128
That's right, you gump-faced,
blown-up, baboon-assed bastard!

1633
01:33:13.173 --> 01:33:14.705
Oh.

1634
01:33:15.931 --> 01:33:19.634
One more outburst like that,
I'll hold you in contempt of court.

1635
01:33:19.681 --> 01:33:21.126
You understand?

1636
01:33:21.399 --> 01:33:22.860
Yes, sir.

1637
01:33:24.767 --> 01:33:26.181
Lord!

1638
01:33:26.755 --> 01:33:28.743
Next witness, please.

1639
01:33:31.142 --> 01:33:35.457
<i>Did you know that you were pregnant
at the time you left Valdosta?</i>

1640
01:33:35.496 --> 01:33:36.735
<i>Yes.</i>

1641
01:33:36.806 --> 01:33:37.970
<i>And yet...</i>

1642
01:33:38.001 --> 01:33:41.149
<i>you tell us over and over...</i>

1643
01:33:41.251 --> 01:33:44.314
<i>that you went with this woman...</i>

1644
01:33:44.384 --> 01:33:45.931
willingly?

1645
01:33:46.243 --> 01:33:50.001
Yes, I wouldn't raise my child
with Frank Bennett.

1646
01:33:50.046 --> 01:33:52.051
<i>But, why?</i>

1647
01:33:52.204 --> 01:33:55.163
<i>Did this woman promise you money?</i>

1648
01:33:55.225 --> 01:33:56.470
No.

1649
01:33:56.549 --> 01:33:58.587
<i>A bigger home?</i>

1650
01:33:59.137 --> 01:34:00.634
No.

1651
01:34:00.853 --> 01:34:02.173
No.

1652
01:34:02.290 --> 01:34:04.860
<i>Then tell us, Mrs. Bennett,</i>

1653
01:34:05.032 --> 01:34:07.745
<i>why would a respectable
Christian woman...</i>

1654
01:34:07.792 --> 01:34:10.120
<i>go anywhere with this
Idgie Threadgoode,...</i>

1655
01:34:10.159 --> 01:34:12.393
<i>- whose reputation is known
- Objection!</i>

1656
01:34:12.425 --> 01:34:16.333
- far and wide as a notorious liar...
- Objection sustained.

1657
01:34:20.740 --> 01:34:25.950
<i>Why did you leave with
Idgie Threadgoode that day?</i>

1658
01:34:28.407 --> 01:34:30.911
<i>Answer the question, Mrs. Bennett.</i>

1659
01:34:32.619 --> 01:34:34.478
Because she...

1660
01:34:38.256 --> 01:34:40.861
she's the best friend I ever had.

1661
01:34:40.910 --> 01:34:42.626
And I love her.

1662
01:34:43.991 --> 01:34:46.291
<i>Thank you, Mrs. Bennett.
That will be all.</i>

1663
01:34:46.374 --> 01:34:49.572
<i>The defense calls as its last witness,...</i>

1664
01:34:49.658 --> 01:34:52.806
the Reverend Herbert Scroggins.

1665
01:34:54.533 --> 01:34:56.916
Place your right hand on the Bible,
please, Reverend.

1666
01:34:56.963 --> 01:34:59.611
I brought my own,
if you don't mind.

1667
01:35:00.805 --> 01:35:04.141
Do you swear to tell the whole truth
and nothing but the truth?

1668
01:35:04.186 --> 01:35:05.665
I do.

1669
01:35:08.612 --> 01:35:12.110
<i>Do you have information
about the whereabouts of...</i>

1670
01:35:12.157 --> 01:35:14.559
<i>Idgie Threadgoode
and her coloured man,</i>

1671
01:35:14.607 --> 01:35:16.161
known as Big George,...

1672
01:35:16.231 --> 01:35:20.262
on the night of
September 30th, 1933?

1673
01:35:20.336 --> 01:35:21.801
Yes, sir, I do.

1674
01:35:21.857 --> 01:35:24.411
<i>Really?
It has been suggested here...</i>

1675
01:35:24.481 --> 01:35:27.864
<i>that she and her coloured man
were at her mother's house.</i>

1676
01:35:27.975 --> 01:35:29.756
<i>Can you confirm that?</i>

1677
01:35:29.883 --> 01:35:31.295
No, sir.

1678
01:35:31.444 --> 01:35:33.194
That is a lie.

1679
01:35:33.280 --> 01:35:34.811
Oh, shit.

1680
01:35:35.069 --> 01:35:36.624
<i>It has been my habit...</i>

1681
01:35:36.687 --> 01:35:38.444
<i>to write down all the dates...</i>

1682
01:35:38.475 --> 01:35:41.296
<i>of the activities of
the church in my Bible.</i>

1683
01:35:41.379 --> 01:35:46.217
<i>And I show that the night
of September 30th, 1933...</i>

1684
01:35:46.291 --> 01:35:49.124
was the start of our annual revival...

1685
01:35:49.194 --> 01:35:51.749
down at the Baptist camp ground.

1686
01:35:52.426 --> 01:35:54.890
Sister Threadgoode was there,...

1687
01:35:55.027 --> 01:35:58.332
<i>along with her hired man,
George Pullman,...</i>

1688
01:35:58.512 --> 01:36:01.052
who was in charge of the barbecue,...

1689
01:36:01.152 --> 01:36:03.238
just as he has been every year

1690
01:36:03.270 --> 01:36:05.520
<i>- for the last ten years.
- Objection!</i>

1691
01:36:05.559 --> 01:36:06.926
That doesn't mean anything.

1692
01:36:06.965 --> 01:36:10.067
Murder could have taken place
any time in the next few days.

1693
01:36:10.121 --> 01:36:13.270
Have you ever been
to one of our revivals, sir?

1694
01:36:13.324 --> 01:36:14.903
<i>Well, no.</i>

1695
01:36:15.106 --> 01:36:18.137
Do you attend church regularly, sir?

1696
01:36:18.231 --> 01:36:19.590
Of course, I do.

1697
01:36:19.676 --> 01:36:20.926
<i>Good.</i>

1698
01:36:21.035 --> 01:36:24.098
<i>Well, maybe if you attended
one of our revivals,...</i>

1699
01:36:24.153 --> 01:36:28.044
you'd know they last
three days and three nights.

1700
01:36:28.089 --> 01:36:29.543
Your Honour.

1701
01:36:32.186 --> 01:36:34.444
<i>Approach the bench.</i>

1702
01:36:34.882 --> 01:36:36.061
Percy,...

1703
01:36:36.108 --> 01:36:38.795
it don't look like
you've got a case at all.

1704
01:36:38.904 --> 01:36:41.397
In the first place, there's no body.

1705
01:36:41.475 --> 01:36:44.826
Second, we've got us a preacher
nobody's going to dispute.

1706
01:36:44.873 --> 01:36:47.654
- But, Your Honour--
- I'm telling you what you've got...

1707
01:36:47.701 --> 01:36:49.592
is a whole lot of nothing.

1708
01:36:49.733 --> 01:36:52.295
<i>I say Frank Bennett
got himself drunk,...</i>

1709
01:36:52.413 --> 01:36:54.186
<i>drove into the river...</i>

1710
01:36:54.264 --> 01:36:55.990
<i>and was long ago eaten up.</i>

1711
01:36:56.022 --> 01:36:59.686
And I don't give
a good goddamn!

1712
01:36:59.928 --> 01:37:03.405
What we got us here
is a case of accidental death.

1713
01:37:03.455 --> 01:37:05.342
Case dismissed!

1714
01:37:05.413 --> 01:37:06.725
Whoo!

1715
01:37:14.542 --> 01:37:17.075
See you in church, sister?

1716
01:37:18.233 --> 01:37:19.919
Reverend.

1717
01:37:20.708 --> 01:37:24.012
I can't believe he actually
swore on the Bible.

1718
01:37:25.090 --> 01:37:27.012
Well, not really.

1719
01:37:27.076 --> 01:37:28.965
If that judge had looked any closer,...

1720
01:37:29.013 --> 01:37:32.325
he'd have seen it was really
a copy of Moby Dick.

1721
01:37:34.367 --> 01:37:36.395
But, why did he do it?

1722
01:37:36.462 --> 01:37:38.668
For the sheer joy of
seeing you in church again,...

1723
01:37:38.724 --> 01:37:41.583
which I suggested to him
might be your penance.

1724
01:37:41.629 --> 01:37:44.192
- You didn't promise him?
- Yes, ma'am, I did.

1725
01:37:44.229 --> 01:37:46.176
And I never break my word.

1726
01:37:46.231 --> 01:37:50.544
If I live a thousand years,
I will never forgive you for this.

1727
01:37:50.685 --> 01:37:53.398
I don't know what's worse,
church or jail.

1728
01:38:06.075 --> 01:38:07.513
There now.

1729
01:38:07.622 --> 01:38:09.427
Don't you look pretty?

1730
01:38:09.583 --> 01:38:11.419
Oh, yes, honey.

1731
01:38:11.833 --> 01:38:15.621
You'll have me looking like
Ginger Rogers before you're done.

1732
01:38:15.802 --> 01:38:17.957
But, don't let Mr. Dunaway see me.

1733
01:38:17.997 --> 01:38:20.426
He's liable to go wild.

1734
01:38:21.755 --> 01:38:24.801
Well, I'm glad to see
you're in a good mood.

1735
01:38:24.950 --> 01:38:27.895
And you've slimmed down quite a bit
in the last few weeks.

1736
01:38:27.973 --> 01:38:29.895
I'm just so happy...

1737
01:38:29.958 --> 01:38:32.505
Big George and Idgie got off.

1738
01:38:32.598 --> 01:38:35.598
I would have killed
Frank Bennett if I could.

1739
01:38:35.739 --> 01:38:38.216
Did anybody really think she did it?

1740
01:38:38.341 --> 01:38:40.840
Some said yes, some said no.

1741
01:38:41.028 --> 01:38:44.059
Of course, the only one who
really knew was Frank Bennett.

1742
01:38:44.145 --> 01:38:45.973
And you know what they say.

1743
01:38:46.083 --> 01:38:49.012
Dead men tell no tales.

1744
01:38:50.237 --> 01:38:53.105
Towanda!

1745
01:39:16.245 --> 01:39:18.823
Evelyn, what in the hell
are you doing?

1746
01:39:18.859 --> 01:39:20.909
I need some light and air.

1747
01:39:21.959 --> 01:39:23.580
Why don't you step outside...

1748
01:39:23.611 --> 01:39:25.650
and take one of your walks
or your jog or...

1749
01:39:25.690 --> 01:39:27.675
whatever it is you do?

1750
01:39:28.779 --> 01:39:31.090
And there's no dinner, either!

1751
01:39:31.730 --> 01:39:33.910
Ed, you have any idea...

1752
01:39:33.949 --> 01:39:36.191
why I've been going
to all these classes?

