Honey, I just...

2014
01:55:35.317 --> 01:55:36.471
feel sorry about...

2015
01:55:36.510 --> 01:55:38.247
the past few months,
you know?

2016
01:55:38.395 --> 01:55:40.174
I don't know what you're really up to,...

2017
01:55:40.229 --> 01:55:42.174
what's going on with you, but...

2018
01:55:42.506 --> 01:55:45.522
I guess I could have been more helpful
with your job and everything.

2019
01:55:45.651 --> 01:55:46.952
You know?

2020
01:55:48.092 --> 01:55:49.866
Well, why are you uh...

2021
01:55:49.952 --> 01:55:53.092
Why are you putting up this wall
where you just tore one down?

2022
01:55:53.140 --> 01:55:54.358
Well...

2023
01:55:54.592 --> 01:55:56.475
I changed my mind.

2024
01:55:56.678 --> 01:55:58.163
Well, I don't mean to seem...

2025
01:55:58.226 --> 01:56:01.015
dense or anything,
but what's changed?

2026
01:56:01.118 --> 01:56:03.123
The air and the light.

2027
01:56:05.565 --> 01:56:07.075
Ed...

2028
01:56:08.282 --> 01:56:10.639
You remember how
you used to tell me...

2029
01:56:10.700 --> 01:56:13.366
you always wanted
two women in your house?

2030
01:56:13.428 --> 01:56:14.971
Oh, God.

2031
01:56:15.908 --> 01:56:17.346
Yeah.

2032
01:56:17.689 --> 01:56:19.049
Well...

2033
01:56:19.684 --> 01:56:22.557
what if I was the younger of the two?

2034
01:56:23.059 --> 01:56:25.385
I don't believe I get your drift.

2035
01:56:26.273 --> 01:56:30.198
I want something more than
I've ever wanted anything before.

2036
01:56:31.012 --> 01:56:33.537
I want to bring Mrs. Threadgoode...

2037
01:56:33.792 --> 01:56:35.441
to our home.

2038
01:56:36.085 --> 01:56:38.399
I want her to live here with us.

2039
01:56:38.825 --> 01:56:41.242
I want to give her the love
she's given me.

2040
01:56:42.370 --> 01:56:43.729
You're kidding me, aren't you?

2041
01:56:43.775 --> 01:56:45.828
I'm absolutely serious.

2042
01:56:46.076 --> 01:56:49.158
That's why I'm putting the wall
to Kyle's room back up.

2043
01:56:50.450 --> 01:56:51.678
Well, honey.

2044
01:56:51.938 --> 01:56:54.413
This isn't something
you're just gonna do. I mean...

2045
01:56:54.506 --> 01:56:56.053
She's an old woman.

2046
01:56:56.385 --> 01:56:57.920
What if she got sick or something?

2047
01:56:57.967 --> 01:56:59.893
I mean, who, who's
gonna take care of her?

2048
01:56:59.929 --> 01:57:01.321
I will.

2049
01:57:01.476 --> 01:57:03.744
I can't leave her in that place.

2050
01:57:03.829 --> 01:57:07.200
She's not a stray cat or something.
Hell, she isn't even family.

2051
01:57:07.311 --> 01:57:09.981
- She's family to me.
- Now, Evelyn.

2052
01:57:11.427 --> 01:57:12.809
Evelyn.

2053
01:57:14.571 --> 01:57:15.950
Honey.

2054
01:57:16.527 --> 01:57:18.215
Uh, look.

2055
01:57:18.331 --> 01:57:20.309
Have, have, have you mentioned this...

2056
01:57:20.410 --> 01:57:22.911
harebrained idea of yours to her?

2057
01:57:22.958 --> 01:57:24.301
Not yet.

2058
01:57:24.364 --> 01:57:25.856
Well, good.

2059
01:57:25.991 --> 01:57:28.395
Then we'll just pretend
it never happened.

2060
01:57:28.450 --> 01:57:31.598
I'm making my own money now.
I'll pay for everything.

2061
01:57:31.660 --> 01:57:34.090
You don't have to do a thing.

2062
01:57:35.322 --> 01:57:36.793
Evelyn...

2063
01:57:38.319 --> 01:57:40.270
it's never gonna happen.

2064
01:57:40.321 --> 01:57:42.270
So, just forget about it.

2065
01:57:44.575 --> 01:57:47.323
Don't you ever say "never" to me.

2066
01:57:56.429 --> 01:57:59.105
Someone helped put a mirror up
in front of my face.

2067
01:57:59.195 --> 01:58:01.668
And I didn't like what I saw one bit.

2068
01:58:01.828 --> 01:58:03.480
And you know what I did?

2069
01:58:03.644 --> 01:58:05.347
I changed.

2070
01:58:05.872 --> 01:58:07.465
And that someone...

2071
01:58:07.543 --> 01:58:09.535
was Mrs. Threadgoode.

2072
01:58:09.738 --> 01:58:11.691
She needs my love and care now.

2073
01:58:11.729 --> 01:58:13.722
And I'm gonna give it to her.

2074
01:58:15.959 --> 01:58:18.938
Now, if you'll excuse me,
I have to go to the gym.

2075
01:58:25.783 --> 01:58:27.673
And if you won't listen to reason,...

2076
01:58:27.731 --> 01:58:30.212
there's always Towanda.

2077
01:58:42.618 --> 01:58:44.282
I knew that.

2078
01:58:44.978 --> 01:58:46.126
<i>Listen.</i>

2079
01:58:46.171 --> 01:58:47.878
Hey, Nin--

2080
01:58:52.167 --> 01:58:54.058
What are you doing?

2081
01:58:54.801 --> 01:58:56.394
Those are her things.

2082
01:58:56.433 --> 01:58:57.909
Those are Mrs. Threadgoode's things.

2083
01:58:57.941 --> 01:58:59.933
What are you doing in here?
Where is Mrs. Threadgoode?

2084
01:58:59.967 --> 01:59:00.972
Who?

2085
01:59:01.006 --> 01:59:03.292
Mrs. Threadgoode,
the woman who lives here.

2086
01:59:03.324 --> 01:59:04.402
Are you deaf?

2087
01:59:04.433 --> 01:59:05.697
I'm sorry, miss.

2088
01:59:05.722 --> 01:59:06.896
All they told me was

2089
01:59:06.921 --> 01:59:09.546
that the woman who lived
in here died this morning.

2090
01:59:12.764 --> 01:59:14.622
Oh, my God.

2091
01:59:14.939 --> 01:59:16.364
What...

2092
01:59:17.531 --> 01:59:19.224
What are you saying?

2093
01:59:19.306 --> 01:59:21.521
<i>Well, she died early this morning.</i>

2094
01:59:21.597 --> 01:59:23.778
They were short-handed,
so they asked me to...

2095
01:59:23.818 --> 01:59:26.192
take all this stuff down.
That's all I know.

2096
01:59:47.840 --> 01:59:49.598
Stop that!

2097
01:59:49.740 --> 01:59:51.950
What is the matter with you people?

2098
01:59:52.300 --> 01:59:55.231
Can't you wait a goddamn day,
for Christ's sake?

2099
01:59:55.300 --> 01:59:57.270
Do you have no respect?

2100
01:59:57.309 --> 01:59:58.817
These are her things!

2101
01:59:58.863 --> 02:00:02.340
Well, I'm sorry, miss, but they told me
to get this room ready for another patient.

2102
02:00:02.373 --> 02:00:04.856
Well, she may be just
another patient to you,...

2103
02:00:04.911 --> 02:00:06.919
but she was my friend.

2104
02:00:06.975 --> 02:00:08.606
And I loved her.

2105
02:00:08.649 --> 02:00:09.933
Sorry.

2106
02:00:10.036 --> 02:00:11.379
I'm just following orders.

2107
02:00:11.418 --> 02:00:13.402
What is going on here?

2108
02:00:13.442 --> 02:00:14.848
Why didn't you call me?

2109
02:00:14.888 --> 02:00:16.450
You could have at least called me

2110
02:00:16.475 --> 02:00:18.456
- before you sent that idiot here.
- I'm sorry, Mrs. Couch.

2111
02:00:18.481 --> 02:00:21.348
It just never occurred to me
that you would take it this hard.

2112
02:00:21.376 --> 02:00:23.606
I didn't even get
to tell her goodbye.

2113
02:00:23.669 --> 02:00:26.419
Oh, I know,
these things are difficult.

2114
02:00:26.450 --> 02:00:28.895
But, she died peacefully in her sleep.

2115
02:00:28.969 --> 02:00:32.575
And to tell the truth, I thought
you'd be happy for Mrs. Threadgoode.

2116
02:00:32.616 --> 02:00:34.168
- Happy?
- Why, yes.

2117
02:00:34.184 --> 02:00:37.207
- This is what she wanted.
- What, to be dead?

2118
02:00:37.268 --> 02:00:39.332
No, to go home.
You just missed her.

2119
02:00:39.373 --> 02:00:42.356
She left in a yellow cab
about a half-hour ago.

2120
02:00:42.475 --> 02:00:44.114
I don't understand.

2121
02:00:44.200 --> 02:00:45.468
What, a cab?

2122
02:00:45.522 --> 02:00:48.163
Well, yeah. She said there wasn't
no reason for her to stay

2123
02:00:48.195 --> 02:00:50.070
now that Mrs. Otis had died.

2124
02:00:50.183 --> 02:00:51.614
Mrs...

2125
02:00:52.411 --> 02:00:54.481
Otis is dead?

2126
02:00:55.665 --> 02:00:58.246
Wow, Mrs. Otis died.

2127
02:00:58.347 --> 02:01:00.393
Mrs. Otis died!

2128
02:01:00.439 --> 02:01:01.520
Mrs. Otis!

2129
02:01:01.559 --> 02:01:02.802
Oh, God!

2130
02:01:02.827 --> 02:01:03.981
Mrs. O--

2131
02:01:04.018 --> 02:01:06.528
Not that I'm,
I'm glad that Mrs. Otis died.

2132
02:01:06.553 --> 02:01:07.967
It's just--
Oh, God.

2133
02:01:08.024 --> 02:01:10.238
Oh, God.
I've got to stop her.

2134
02:01:10.277 --> 02:01:11.699
Oh.

2135
02:01:49.947 --> 02:01:51.254
Hey, Evelyn.

2136
02:01:51.317 --> 02:01:53.277
Somebody stole my house.

2137
02:01:53.421 --> 02:01:55.973
It was right here when I left.

2138
02:01:56.213 --> 02:01:57.449
Unless--

2139
02:01:57.519 --> 02:01:58.801
Oh, Evelyn.

2140
02:01:58.855 --> 02:02:01.496
You don't reckon
I'm crazy, do you?

2141
02:02:01.736 --> 02:02:03.613
It was here when I left.

2142
02:02:03.644 --> 02:02:05.559
No, honey, you're not crazy.

2143
02:02:05.605 --> 02:02:07.348
This is the place.

2144
02:02:08.238 --> 02:02:11.801
Well, why would anyone want
to steal an old lady's home?

2145
02:02:12.321 --> 02:02:14.223
It wasn't worth nothing.

2146
02:02:14.340 --> 02:02:15.856
Oh, honey.

2147
02:02:15.996 --> 02:02:17.863
Nobody stole it.

2148
02:02:18.004 --> 02:02:20.121
They had to tear it down.

2149
02:02:20.288 --> 02:02:22.129
It was condemned.

2150
02:02:22.525 --> 02:02:24.840
I'm sorry.
I should have told you.

2151
02:02:24.926 --> 02:02:27.324
Well, somebody should have told me.

2152
02:02:27.519 --> 02:02:29.824
I'm old.
I'm, I'm not a child.

2153
02:02:29.869 --> 02:02:31.387
I'm sorry.

2154
02:02:32.465 --> 02:02:35.659
My husband, Cleo, and I
lived in this house for...

2155
02:02:35.862 --> 02:02:37.823
more than 40 years.

2156
02:02:38.328 --> 02:02:40.744
Now it's, it's gone.

2157
02:02:41.963 --> 02:02:44.532
83 years worth of living...

2158
02:02:44.607 --> 02:02:47.067
and all that's left of me
is what's in this box.

2159
02:02:47.128 --> 02:02:49.684
A bunch of old cards and pictures.

2160
02:02:49.887 --> 02:02:51.043
Come on.

2161
02:02:51.098 --> 02:02:52.184
I'll take you home.

2162
02:02:52.218 --> 02:02:54.082
This is my home!

2163
02:02:54.251 --> 02:02:55.965
And now it's gone.

2164
02:02:56.285 --> 02:02:58.738
And Mrs. Otis has gone.

2165
02:02:58.958 --> 02:03:00.442
Yeah.

2166
02:03:01.105 --> 02:03:03.613
I, I don't quite know
what to do. I...

2167
02:03:03.817 --> 02:03:07.996
This is the first time I can remember
when I don't have a soul to look after.

2168
02:03:08.195 --> 02:03:10.449
You can come look after me and Ed.

2169
02:03:10.536 --> 02:03:12.152
Oh, you're sweet.

2170
02:03:12.191 --> 02:03:15.606
But, I think you're doing
just fine on your own.

2171
02:03:15.844 --> 02:03:19.012
Don't you know
you'd be like a gift for us?

2172
02:03:19.831 --> 02:03:22.636
You're the reason
I get up every morning.

2173
02:03:23.020 --> 02:03:26.059
And that Mary Kay's having
such a good year.

2174
02:03:26.340 --> 02:03:30.606
And that I don't look like
some blob from a horror movie.

2175
02:03:31.044 --> 02:03:34.090
Well, with a little help
from Idgie and Ruth.

2176
02:03:35.137 --> 02:03:36.629
Come on.

2177
02:03:36.746 --> 02:03:39.067
I've got your room all ready.

2178
02:03:39.307 --> 02:03:41.762
What does Ed say about all this?

2179
02:03:41.873 --> 02:03:43.848
He'll learn to love it.

2180
02:03:49.138 --> 02:03:50.716
Did I ever tell you...

2181
02:03:50.841 --> 02:03:53.294
that Mrs. Otis was
Sipsey's baby sister?

2182
02:03:53.317 --> 02:03:55.544
- No, ma'am.
- Yes, she was.

2183
02:03:55.934 --> 02:03:59.809
Mrs. Otis was with Sipsey and me
the night Sipsey died.

2184
02:04:00.089 --> 02:04:05.286
Sipsey told me a story that night
I've never told a living soul, Evelyn.

2185
02:04:05.618 --> 02:04:08.302
<i>The story about what really happened...</i>

2186
02:04:08.411 --> 02:04:11.232
<i>the night Frank Bennett disappeared.</i>

2187
02:04:44.194 --> 02:04:45.545
- Hi, there.
- Miss Idgie,

2188
02:04:45.585 --> 02:04:47.124
you've got to come quick.

2189
02:04:47.742 --> 02:04:48.937
Well...

2190
02:04:48.987 --> 02:04:50.733
the show's hardly begun.

2191
02:04:50.871 --> 02:04:53.485
You've got to come quick now,
you hear me?

2192
02:04:58.570 --> 02:04:59.999
Run now and get help!

2193
02:05:00.039 --> 02:05:01.597
- Go get help, quick!
- Where's the baby?

2194
02:05:01.628 --> 02:05:03.188
- Run!
- Never mind.

2195
02:05:22.734 --> 02:05:24.508
Excuse me, sir.

2196
02:05:24.859 --> 02:05:28.523
I don't believe you should be
going anywhere with Ruth's baby.

2197
02:05:41.279 --> 02:05:43.685
Like I said,
you ain't going nowhere.

2198
02:05:43.724 --> 02:05:46.904
Damn, you're a thick-headed
son of a bitch, ain't you?

2199
02:05:51.792 --> 02:05:56.126
I told you you ain't going nowheres
with Miss Ruth's baby.

2200
02:06:02.453 --> 02:06:03.874
Come on, angel.

2201
02:06:03.906 --> 02:06:05.086
Come on.

2202
02:06:05.127 --> 02:06:06.781
Come on, sweetheart.

2203
02:06:06.880 --> 02:06:08.499
It's all right.

2204
02:06:08.828 --> 02:06:10.015
Come on.

2205
02:06:10.062 --> 02:06:11.960
It's all right, baby.

2206
02:06:14.741 --> 02:06:17.079
<i>It was self-defense.</i>

2207
02:06:17.581 --> 02:06:21.618
I don't know why any white jury
would care why I did it.

2208
02:06:21.796 --> 02:06:24.814
- Well, I saw it, and I can testify.
- Uh, excuse me here.

2209
02:06:24.858 --> 02:06:26.863
I don't mean no offense here.

2210
02:06:26.930 --> 02:06:30.064
But, I don't know who is less
likely to convince the jury,...

2211
02:06:30.111 --> 02:06:31.603
my mama...

2212
02:06:31.681 --> 02:06:33.545
or Mr. Smokey here.

2213
02:06:33.664 --> 02:06:35.431
No offense taken.

2214
02:06:35.941 --> 02:06:37.962
You're a good man, Mr. Smokey.

2215
02:06:38.014 --> 02:06:39.079
You did good.

2216
02:06:39.110 --> 02:06:41.228
The sun's almost up.

2217
02:06:45.368 --> 02:06:46.501
George?

2218
02:06:46.548 --> 02:06:47.899
Mmm-hmm.

2219
02:06:49.380 --> 02:06:51.118
I think...

2220
02:06:51.531 --> 02:06:53.977
it's hog-boiling time.

2221
02:06:55.131 --> 02:06:56.914
God, no, ma'am.

2222
02:06:56.968 --> 02:06:59.710
- It ain't cold enough.
- It's hog-boiling time.

2223
02:07:04.561 --> 02:07:06.443
- Hey, George?
- Uh-huh.

2224
02:07:06.481 --> 02:07:08.404
When is that barbecue
gonna be ready?

2225
02:07:08.442 --> 02:07:10.638
Oh, it's gonna be ready
any time now.

2226
02:07:10.779 --> 02:07:13.638
It smells so damn good.
I just can't wait to get me some.

2227
02:07:15.768 --> 02:07:18.193
Now, don't you forget to call me
when that's ready.

2228
02:07:18.233 --> 02:07:19.742
All right.

2229
02:07:33.704 --> 02:07:35.423
Here you go.

2230
02:07:37.652 --> 02:07:39.657
- Miss Idgie.
- Yeah.

2231
02:07:39.802 --> 02:07:41.658
Smokey left town.

2232
02:07:41.970 --> 02:07:44.697
I thought it'd be best
under the circumstances.

2233
02:07:45.480 --> 02:07:48.072
He asked that
you tell Ruth goodbye.

2234
02:07:49.464 --> 02:07:51.541
Shame he had to go.

2235
02:08:00.881 --> 02:08:02.366
Hold on!

2236
02:08:02.475 --> 02:08:04.077
I'm coming.

2237
02:08:08.774 --> 02:08:09.844
What you want?

2238
02:08:09.883 --> 02:08:11.399
We want some barbecue.

2239
02:08:11.430 --> 02:08:12.852
Oh, not today, you don't.

2240
02:08:12.884 --> 02:08:14.259
Go on, now.

2241
02:08:28.879 --> 02:08:32.143
Why, this is about
the best barbecue I ever ate.

2242
02:08:33.644 --> 02:08:35.769
The secret's in the sauce.

2243
02:08:45.252 --> 02:08:46.904
Sipsey?

2244
02:08:47.341 --> 02:08:48.935
My God.

2245
02:08:49.008 --> 02:08:52.693
That frying pan did more
than fry chicken that night.

2246
02:08:53.928 --> 02:08:55.264
Oh.

2247
02:08:55.326 --> 02:08:58.201
Did Idgie really barbecue
Frank Bennett?

2248
02:08:58.269 --> 02:08:59.889
Oh, you're pulling my leg.

2249
02:08:59.930 --> 02:09:03.060
Secret's in the sauce,
or so I've been told.

2250
02:09:06.937 --> 02:09:10.572
Now you know why
Idgie had to go on trial.

2251
02:09:10.875 --> 02:09:13.291
She knew the law would
never believe Sipsey.

2252
02:09:13.346 --> 02:09:14.456
No!

2253
02:09:14.518 --> 02:09:17.283
Sipsey or Big George
or anyone else of colour

2254
02:09:17.315 --> 02:09:19.237
would have been hanging
from the nearest tree.

2255
02:09:19.275 --> 02:09:20.478
Mmm.

2256
02:09:20.697 --> 02:09:21.885
To this day,

2257
02:09:21.925 --> 02:09:25.620
I'm still not sure whether
Ruth ever believed that...

2258
02:09:25.719 --> 02:09:28.557
Idgie didn't kill Frank Bennett.

2259
02:09:29.839 --> 02:09:32.761
Truth's a funny thing sometimes.

2260
02:09:34.878 --> 02:09:36.456
I feel better now.

2261
02:09:36.501 --> 02:09:37.846
Good.

2262
02:09:38.207 --> 02:09:41.526
I feel better because
all these people will live...

2263
02:09:41.628 --> 02:09:43.815
as long as you remember them.

2264
02:09:44.742 --> 02:09:46.483
You reminded me...

2265
02:09:46.655 --> 02:09:49.921
about what the most
important thing in life is.

2266
02:09:50.225 --> 02:09:52.436
- You know what I think it is?
- No, ma'am.

2267
02:09:52.585 --> 02:09:53.905
